  "text": "• Hypothyroidism: Paresthesia is a more frequent clinical manifestation observed in hypothyroidism [CITATION_1] 97) . About 40% of hypothyroid patients have predominantly sensory signs of a sensorimotor axonal neuropathy early in the course of thyroid disease. It appears that the axonal myelin sheath begins to degenerate without sufficient thyroid hormone, and regeneration of damaged nerves also slows (98).",
